    Zinka Kunc Milanov (1906-1989), a Croatian soprano (also of Slovene descent on her father's side), is still considered one of the greatest singers of the 20th century. She made her debut at the Ljubljana Opera with the Volgo Leonore in Verdi's Troubadour. She spent most of her career singing at the New York Metropolitan Opera. She became famous for her roles as Aida, Leonora, Tosca, Norma and Gioconda. Together with his brother, composer and pianist Božidar Kunc, they also performed Slovenian songs.
